  "articleSummary": "The article argues that AI agents are useless without the ability to integrate with external systems like Salesforce or Jira, and that the Model Context Protocol (MCP) solves this by standardizing tool connections—analogous to USB-C for cables. It explains how MCP eliminates the need for custom API wrappers, using Mastra’s `MCPClient` to connect local and remote tools with minimal code. The tutorial-style piece also covers per-user authentication for multi-tenant security and composite tools, targeting developers building production-ready agents.",
